subSections.title: Han character
subSections.text:
{{Han char|rn=140|rad=艸|as=8|sn=11|four=|canj=TOGG|ids=⿱艹佳}}

This character is found in some character sets (see below), but its reading and meaning are unknown.

subSections.title: References
subSections.text: {{Han ref|kx=|dkj=|dj=|hdz=|uh=9FBF}} This character is found in the following character sets: * [https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2018/18096-telegraph-upd.pdf#page=33 5495] in China's ''Standard Telegraph Codebook'' (标准电码本（修订本）, 1983) * [https://www.cns11643.gov.tw/wordView.jsp?ID=742238 11-535E] in Taiwan's CNS 11643 character set ** This website claims that the Mandarin reading is ''jiā'', which seems to be a guess from the bottom component [[佳]] (''jiā''). This reading is not found in other sources. * [http://dict.cbeta.org/word/search.php?op=search&cb=06229 CB06229] in Taiwan's CBETA [[gaiji]] character set * [https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2007/07067r-sevencjkall.pdf 7666] in Japan's ''Sha-ken'' ({{lang|ja|写研}}) character collection, which is the source of Adobe-Japan1 CID+20068 * [https://mojikiban.ipa.go.jp/search/detail/MJ060118 J+B9C0] in Japan's ''Jūki Net Unified Character Code'' ({{lang|ja|住基ネット統一文字コード}}) * [http://www.koreanhistory.or.kr/newchar/list_view.jsp?code=73772 KC03579] in Korea's ''Newly Found Hanja'' (신출한자) ** This website claims that the Korean reading is 추, which seems to be a(n incorrect) guess from [[隹]] (추; not 佳, whose reading is 가). This reading is not found in other sources. ** It also claims that the (Korean) meaning is "abundance of grass" (풀이 많은 모양), but this meaning is not found in other sources.
